<bioghist altrender="biography" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
	<head>Biography</head>
	<p><persname>Peter Lukoff</persname>, of <geogname>Norwich, Connecticut</geogname>, served in Company C, 48th Armor Infantry Battalion date from April 1944 through June 1945.   Prior to his war service he was employed by the <corpname>Hartford-Connecticut Trust Company</corpname>, Thames Branch.</p>

<p></p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
	<head>Scope and Content</head>
	<p>The bulk of the collection documents Lukoff's experiences from training in the <geogname>United States</geogname> (<geogname>South Carolina</geogname>) and his activities in <geogname>France</geogname>, <geogname>Belgium</geogname>, <geogname>Germany</geogname> and <geogname>England</geogname>. Also included are letters and cards from his wife, Alma, and two children, Philip and Barbara. Lukoff was wounded in action at the Battle of the Bulge and separated from his unit for a short period of time. </p>
</scopecontent>
